<headline>Special Weather Statement issued February 18 at 6:17AM EST  by NWS Albany</headline>
<description>...ICY ROADS AND SURFACES POSSIBLE THIS MORNING...
The combination of recent rain and rapidly falling temperatures
behind a cold front could produce some icy conditions on untreated
roads and walking surfaces. Temperatures in the 50s ahead of the
cold front are plunging into the 20s behind the front, and may
produce patches of black ice, especially on roads that may have
leftover standing water from the recent rain that will quickly
turn to ice. Use extra caution if out and about this morning.</description>
